  "texts": [
    "The matrix is entry-wise expressed as P π,ϕ,µ (s′ | s) = a∈A,b∈B P µ (s ′ | s, a, b)π(a | s)ϕ(b | s).We denote by ν π,ϕ,µ the stationary distribution of the Markov chain, which is the singular vector of P π,ϕ,µ associated with the (only) largest singular value \"1 ′′ (under an ergodicity assumption).",
    "Let the discounted visitation/occupancy measure d π, ϕ, µ ρ ≜ E s0∼ρ [d π, ϕ, µ s] under the initial state distribution ρ, whered π, ϕ, µ s ≜ (1 -γ)E π,ϕ,P µ [ ∞ k=0 γ k 1(s k = s) | s 0 = s],where the expectation is taken overa k ∼ π(• | s k), b k ∼ ϕ(• | s k), s k+1 ∼ P µ (• | s k, a k, b k).Under (ϕ, π, µ), the follower expects to collect the following (regularized) cumulative rewardJ f (π, ϕ, µ) ≜ E π,ϕ,P µ ∞ k=0 γ k r f (s k, a k, b k, µ) -τ log π(a k | s k) | s 0 ∼ ρ = 1 1-γ E s∼d π, ϕ, µ ρ, a∼π(•|s), b∼ϕ(•|s) [r f (s, a, b, µ) + τ E(π, s)],(1)where the entropy function E(π, s) ≜a π(a | s) log π(a | s), and regularization weight τ ≥ 0.Define the follower's policy asπ ⋆: ∆ S B × ∆ S → ∆ S A such that π ⋆ (ϕ, µ) ≜ argmax π∈∆ S A J f (π, ϕ, µ), ∀µ.",
    "(2)Let µ ⋆: ∆ S B → ∆ S denote the mapping from the leader's policy to the mean field induced by the leader.",
    "It is known from the literature on standard MFGs that µ ⋆ (ϕ) satisfies for all ϕ µ ⋆ (ϕ) ≜ ν π ⋆ (ϕ,µ ⋆ (ϕ)), ϕ, µ ⋆ (ϕ).",
    "(3)With some abuse of notation, we writeπ ⋆ (ϕ) ≜ π ⋆ (ϕ, µ ⋆ (ϕ)),(4)Fixing the leader's policy to ϕ reduces the environment to a standard MFG among the followers."
